This paper discusses the performance of evolutionary algorithms and probabilistic models in solving optimization problems with epistasis and deception. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
